<item>
            <title>[FLINK-36585] The SplitFetcherManager.close() can chain the futures in a tight loop.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-36585</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is an issue introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-35924&quot; title=&quot;Improve the SourceReaderBase to support the RecordsWithSplitIds share internal buffer from SplitReader.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-35924&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-35924&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The SplitFetcherManager.close() may chain the fetcher status check to the element queue availability future in a tight loop. This may cause problems such as OOM if the fetcher closure takes long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is straightforward. We just need to blocking waiting on each check.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
